en_259347_0	Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe has said that the Chinese Government had never impressed upon Sri Lanka with respect to the Hambanthota Harbour.
en_259347_1	Pointing out that a harbour devoid of ships was made a port in which vessels arrived, the Prime Minister said that it would be transformed into a developed harbour.
en_259347_2	Premier Wickremasinghe made these references making a special statement on the revelation made by the New York Times newspaper with respect to the former President.
en_259347_3	The Prime Minister emphasized that not a single property of the island had been sold to any foreign country.
en_259347_4	He pointed out that even the Hambanthota Harbour had not been sold.
en_259347_5	He said that initially they received a harbour without ships.
en_259347_6	But now ships have begun to arrive and the Harbor is making profits.
en_259347_7	He said that even the Mattala International Airport is to be made a viable venture.
en_259347_8	In the meantime, the Prime Minister pointed out that the National Audit Commission should be looked in a democratic manner.
en_259347_9	He made this reference when the National Audit Bill was taken up for debate in Parliament today.
